@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Uppo" where you want
on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or
Libraries are needed.

NOTE: I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Uppo runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  At the start of a game, a coloured tile pattern is displayed,
and the goal is to move all coloured tiles so they are placed on
the uppermost rows. Try to complete a game in the least amount of
moves...

  To play, click on any tile that is located beside the empty
space, then, the clicked tile will go towards the empty space
(note that you can also use the cursor keys to move the tiles).

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:

 New Game: Restarts the current game board.
 --------

 About:    Displays the informations about the game.
 -----

 Colour:   Changes the colour of the game tiles.
 ------

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

